Package: mtp2bbd
Type: Package
Title: Fast projected Newton-like algorithm and brigde-block decomposition approach for precision matrix estimation under nonnegative partial correlations
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Xiwen Wang, Jiaxi Ying, and Daniel P. Palomar
Maintainer: The package maintainer <yourself@somewhere.net>
Description: The package implements the fast projected Newton-like algorithm together with a brigde-block decomposition approach for precision matrix estimation under nonnegative partial correlations. The package is based on the papers: 
    X. Wang, J. Ying, and D. P. Palomar, ‘Learning Large-Scale MTP2 Gaussian Graphical Models via Bridge-Block Decomposition,’ accepted in Neural Information Processing Systems (NeurIPS), New Orleans, LA, USA, Dec. 2023.
    J.-F. Cai, J. V. de Miranda Cardoso, D. P. Palomar, and J. Ying, "Fast Projected Newton-like Method for Precision Matrix Estimation under Total Positivity", accepted in Neural Information Processing Systems (NeurIPS), New Orleans, LA, USA, Dec. 2023.    
